{"id":"JUDGE-1","severity":"MEDIUM","rule_id":"REQ-2","file":"schedule/__init__.py","line":714,"message":"The run count advances only after job_func returns. If job_func raises, the invocation consumes no budget, so after the caller catches the exception a max_runs(1) job remains scheduled and run_all() invokes it again. Reproduced with two run_all() calls: {'calls': 2, 'jobs_remaining': 1}. This violates the requirement that the budget count actual job_func executions and that an (n+1)th call never happen.","confidence":"high","quoted_evidence":"ret = self.job_func()\n        self.last_run = datetime.datetime.now()\n        self._schedule_next_run()\n        self._run_count += 1"}
# SUMMARY {"verdict":"NEEDS_WORK","notes":"The specified unittest command passes all 87 tests, and the pre-run guard closes the previously reported downward-reconfiguration gap. However, Requirement 2 still fails when job_func raises because the counter increment is skipped, permitting calls beyond the configured budget."}
